decks.notes: The main focus of this Dimir Control deck is to disrupt the opponent's game plan while generating card advantage and maintaining board control through countermagic and removal spells. The deck utilizes powerful cards like Ancestral Recall, Force of Will, and Time Walk to outvalue the opponent, while also employing Urza's Saga to tutor for key artifacts like Time Vault and Sol Ring. Lurrus of the Dream-Den serves as a companion, providing additional value by allowing the player to cast cheap permanents from the graveyard. Overall, the deck aims to control the game tempo and win through incremental advantages.

The main focus of this deck is to disrupt the opponent's game plan with hate cards like Thalia, Guardian of Thraben and Chancellor of the Annex, while also applying pressure with aggressive creatures like Archon of Emeria and White Plume Adventurer. The deck also utilizes mana acceleration with cards like Chrome Mox and the Moxen to quickly deploy threats and disrupt the opponent's mana base with cards like Wasteland. The inclusion of cards like Trinisphere and Chalice of the Void further enhances the disruptive strategy of the deck.
